Thinking how my grandfather worked as a cattle herder when he was 5 years old, at a foreign household in another village because his family had no money to feed him, one time a bull charged him down, stabbed him in the chest, and threw him in the air, no idea how he even survived

He literally was forced to sneak into the neighbors' pigpen at one point, to steal from the pigs' feed, as he would literally starve otherwise... same day before being attacked by the bull he had nearly drowned after a lamb pushed him into a river. Strongest man I ever knew...

It's insane how in Eastern Europe, 2 generations ago people were going to war, hunting down forest animals as not to starve in winter, then our parents for some reason decided to have only 1-2 kids, even being well-off, then our generation came into a strange and unnatural world

Not only Eastern Europe, most of the world honestly, from a traditional and harsh life, into an exciting progress, into the seeming end of history. Villages abandoned, cities blooming and then decaying, old land sitting empty, it's really impossible to contemplate all of it
